NASA is a webbased application from external supplier Omniplan. Internal ING advisors use NASA to draft ING mortgages orientation and advice dossiers.NASA is hosted on two windows servers that host the webappliation, which the internal advisors can access with a browser. The database supporting the application is located on two database servers. The data on both databases is kept in sync.NASA has a couple of external conns:- to PFP, which is a calculation module hosted by the external supplier where financial calculations are performed (without personal data)- to Pricetool, which supplies the actual interest ratesAnd there is an internal connection to HDN-Central, that distributes?the mortgage requests (in our case to Force) and returns processing and status information

In order to boost the RPA business case, in 2019 global robotics team analyzed a cognitive RPA solution is needed.Cognitive RPA: It is technology that can extract, interpret, and classify unstructured data (ready for further processing). Cognitive automation uses one or more of the following techniques: natural language processing, text analytics, data mining, semantic technology and machine learning. While regular RPA technology requires digital structured input data, cognitive RPA can convert semi-structured/unstructured data into structured data. Currently this business application is transforming from project to fully operational in production.https://cs.ing.net/sites/GRPA/SitePages/ABBYYpilot.aspx

Corporate Compliance helps manage conflict of interest in business dealings and in personal account dealings. The business dealings are supported through three control rooms and the personal dealings are managed by a personal account dealing team. The Control Room monitors conflicts of interest in business dealings by obtaining the deal details and persons involved to determine if a deal is conflicted and if restrictions apply or measures need to be taken by the business. Information on the deal and persons involved is provided by the deal captain. The available information is often sensitive and is in many cases price sensitive. In addition, the control room performs research clearance to identify potential conflicts of interest and adequacy of disclosures on publications before publication. The MortgageAffordabilityNLAPI (backend) services serveral Journeys (frontends) concerning the Interest Only dossier. It has multiple functions:1. It retracts information about a specific loan for a specific customer, using the MortgageInquiryAPI. So that the journey can display this information to the user in the desired format.2. It calculates the maximal loan amount using the MortgageMaxLoanCalculatorAPI. So that the journey can display this amount to the user.3. It stores the additional information that is provided by the customor like the pension date and income (optionally using the FinancialPositonsAPI).4. It stores the outcome of the journey like the intentions of the customer and the end-codes of the journey.5. If the journey is started for a second time (in future) then the API displays the end-state of the last session.

SIGMA is a global Compliance Control-Room application whose primary function is the enforcement of the 'Ethical Wall' between the various front office departments at ING.Two main components: the Ethical Wall Information Module and the Surveillance Module.  The Ethical Wall Information Module is a database of all ING's relevant client-transactions.  SIGMA is an ING-UK in-house developed application, running on Windows/SQL. Hosted via ING-UK.Global Compliance teams utilize and access the systems. (Trading) interfaces from various sources, among them from the Americas.Note: the specific US regulatory mandated Employee Trading monitoring functionality will be handled via legacy GMIS and as of May 2014 via Compliance11)

UDA consisting out of different tools used for reporting according to the Basel directives. These tools will get decommissioned over time as GFRS Light?and PSA will take over their functions.?Following tools are part of the UDA:- Funding plan (FundingPlan*.accdb and segmentation for forecast.accdb): access based tool used to create the Funding Plan report as part of Solvency reporting. (Analytical tool, used yearly, CIA 1 1 1)- Ilaap (ILAAP3_20YYMM.accdb ): access based tool used to create the Internal Liquidity Adequacy Assessment Process; Ilaap is a mix between the Basel II LRR and the Basel III LCR reports to be delivered to Amsterdam through the group program GFRS. (Operational tool, used monthly, CIA 1 1 1)- Balance Sheet to LCR (New_LCRtoBS.accdb): access based tool used to transform the accounting data into the right format
